- content_for :page_title do
  ' Startup Alliance – Community Canvas

- content_for :page_header do
  h2.bold.little-space-top.little-space-bottom.white-text.text-center
    ' Community Canvas
.row
  .medium-10.medium-offset-1.columns
    p.snug-top.text-right
      ' Last updated October 30, 2017

    .row
      .medium-3.columns
        p
          em
            ' Like the Business Model and Lean Canvas’ for startups, the
            ' #{link_to 'Community Canvas', 'https://community-canvas.org', target: '_blank' }
            ' was created as a framework to help communities articulate their purpose and maximize
            ' the value they deliver to their membership.
        p
          em
            ' Our Community Canvas will help your understand what we're about and how participation
            ' will benefit you. We welcome your comments and questions.
            '
      .medium-9.columns
        = image_tag 'community_canvas.png'

    .row
      .medium-3.columns
        h4.bold.pad-right.primary-text
          strong Identity:
      .medium-9.columns
        p.bold
          ' Our Purpose
        p
          ' Startup Alliance exists as a community to help global entrepreneurs work together to stay focused and be
          ' more effective, make connections and help each other overcome challenges and maximize their success.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Our Membership
        p
          ' Startup Alliance members are entrepreneurs operating all types of businesses located anywhere
          ' on earth. Additionally, Startup Alliance membership includes business experts including those
          ' providing helpful advice as well as private and institutional investors.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Our Core Values
        p
          ' Startup Alliance values entrepreneurship as one of the greatest powers for good in the world.
          ' Further, Startup Alliance members value collaboration and the generous sharing of information
          ' and ideas with other members in order to help each other maximize their success.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Our Definition of Success
        p
          ' Startup Alliance members are successful when their business goals are met, and their companies
          ' deliver value to their communities and provide a meaningful livelihood to its workers. Startup
          ' Alliance is successful when its members consider their Startup Alliance membership
          ' a factor in their personal and business success.
          '

        p.bold
          ' The Startup Alliance Brand
        p
          ' The Startup Alliance brand is embodied in transparency, clear communication and a genuine desire
          ' to contribute value to the world through encouraging entrepreneurial efforts globally and
          ' in collaboration to maximize each others success.
          '


    .row
      .medium-3.columns
        h4.bold.pad-right.primary-text
          strong Experience:
      .medium-9.columns
        p.bold
          ' Accessing the Startup Alliance
        p
          ' Startup Alliance is an online community — membership is open to entrepreneurs as well as business
          ' advisors and investors who support the entrepreneurs and their companies. Access to the community
          ' and tools provided by Startup Alliance requires members to register and sign-in. Access to certain
          ' features may require payment of subscription fees.
        p
          ' Any member can be invited to join any company team or private alliance. It is up to the member that
          ' listed the company or created the private alliance to decide who receives an invitation. Furthermore,
          ' some companies and private alliances operate in “stealth mode” on Startup Alliance and will not appear
          ' in the directory or in search results. Only the members of those companies and alliances can access
          ' and participate within those entities.
          '

        /p.bold
          ' Rituals
        /p
          '

        p.bold
          ' Membership Experiences
        p
          ' Startup Alliance members collaborate one-on-one with other members and one-to-many within their
          ' company teams and private alliances. Collaboration happens through the written word and real-time
          ' web conferences. Members also use organizational aids and productivity tools to help themselves
          ' and their fellow members. Each member, company and private alliance has a searchable profile to
          ' help people make beneficial connections leading to mutual success.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Community Content
        p
          ' Each member, company and private alliance profile provides insight about their role and activities.
          ' The organizational aids and productivity tools provide a written record of objectives set, outcomes
          ' achieved and progress made. The collaboration tools provide a historical trove of business wisdom
          ' and solutions contributed by the members themselves.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Governing Rules
        p
          ' Membership in the Startup Alliance is governed by our #{link_to 'Code of Conduct', code_of_conduct_path}.
          '

        p.bold
          ' Membership Levels
        p
          /' There are three levels of membership.
          span.bold
            ' Associate Members
          ' can join any company team and private alliance and respond to private messages.
          span.bold
            ' Alliance Members
          ' can do everything Associate Members can as well as create and manage private alliances, manage
          ' their alliance memberships and send private messages to other members.
          span.bold
            ' Company Members
          ' can do everything Alliance Members can as well as create and manage company listings and manage
          ' membership on their company teams.
        p
          ' More specifics on the #{link_to 'Membership Plans', pricing_path} page.

        /p.bold
          ' Transitioning Out
        /p
          ' placeholder
          '


    .row
      .medium-3.columns
        h4.bold.pad-right.primary-text
          strong Structure:
      .medium-9.columns
        p.bold
          ' The Organization
        p
          ' Startup Alliance was founded by #{link_to 'John Knapp', vanity_path('john')} who leads the organization
          ' and oversees its operation. An advisory board of seasoned entrepreneurs and startup experts helps guide
          ' the organization and input from the membership helps prioritize, vet and evaluate new member benefits.
          '

        /p.bold
          ' Governance
        /p
          ' placeholder
          '

        p.bold
          ' The Delivery Platform
        p
          ' Startup Alliance is an online community which exists as a web application. Activities occur
          ' on this site which is globally accessible on the Internet via mobile and desktop devices.
          '

        /p.bold
          ' Data Management
        /p
          ' placeholder
          '

        p.bold
          ' Financing
        p
          ' Startup Alliance is capitalized by the founder and membership subscription fees.
          '

        p &nbsp;
